Please add a feature that allows entity repositories with same class name, targeting different databases on same server.  Its awkward having to create different class names for the same table name when targeting multiple databases.  Could you please implement this feature?

**Desired**
```
@Table(catalog = "Students", name="Person")
@Entity
public class Student

@Table(catalog = "Teachers", name="Person")
@Entity
public class Student
```

**Actual**
```
@Table(catalog = "Students", name="Person")
@Entity
public class TeachersDatabaseStudent

@Table(catalog = "Teachers", name="Person")
@Entity
public class StudentDatabaseStudent
```

